    "The lives of the earlier and Italian artists are partly based on the <em>Vite</em> by <a href=\"/vasarig\">Giorgio Vasari</a>, while his contributions on contemporary Italian, Flemish and Dutch painters, including some from Germany, provide personal accounts of sixteenth-century painting in Italy and in Northern Europe.": [],
    "The final sections of the <em>Schilder-Boeck</em> contain an interpretation of Ovid's <em>Metamorphoses</em>, and a handbook of ancient iconology.": [],
    "Following Van Mander's death (1606), a new edition of the <em>Schilder-Boeck</em> was published in 1616-1618, to which his own biography was added, probably written by his youngest brother, Adam.": [
